---
import Email from "@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/svgs/solid/envelope.svg?raw";
import Pin from "@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/svgs/solid/map-pin.svg?raw";
import Github from "@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/svgs/brands/github.svg?raw";
import Globe from "@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/svgs/solid/globe.svg?raw";
import LinkedIn from "@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/svgs/brands/linkedin.svg?raw";
import Phone from "@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/svgs/solid/phone.svg?raw";
import Check from "@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/svgs/solid/check.svg";
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Resume</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@200;400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content">
        <div class="intro">
          <div class="headshot">
            <img src="/headshot.jpeg" />
          </div>
          <div class="text">
            <h1 class="name">
              <span>
                Ethan Standel
              </span>
            </h1>
            <h2 class="title">
              Senior software engineer
            </h2>
            <p class="about-me">
              Hi, my name is Ethan! I'm a fullstack software engineer focussing on building applications & systems that provide a unique challenge. I love building systems with strict, interesting, thoughtful, or just plain fun requirements in the areas of aesthetic, behavior, scalability, performance, accessibility, internationalization, or themability. I value developer experience, automated workflows, and shipping code over supporting overly customized architecture. I also happen to adore cotton-candy color schemes! Hopefully your organization is looking for engineers who share my interests and values!
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="contact">
          <ul class="left">
            <li>
              <Fragment set:html={Email} />
              <p><a href="mailto:ethan@standel.io">ethan@standel.io</a></p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <Fragment set:html={Phone} />
              <p><a href="tel:2072101127">(207) 210-1127</a></p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <Fragment set:html={Pin} />
              <p>Saco, Maine</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <ul class="right">
            <li>
              <Fragment set:html={Globe} />
              <p><a href="https://www.standel.io">standel.io</a></p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <Fragment set:html={Github} />
              <p><a href="https://github.com/EthanStandel">github.com/EthanStandel</a></p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <Fragment set:html={LinkedIn} />
              <p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ethan-standel/">linkedin.com/in/ethan-standel</a></p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="work-history">
          <h3>Career experience</h3>
          <ul>
            <li class="history-item">
              <h4>Software engineer to Senior software engineer</h4>
              <h5>DEPT® - May 2021 to present</h5>
              <ul class="history-details">
                <li>Worked with my first client in 2021 to transition their site from full CMS to NextJS with a headless CMS. Integrated SSO authentication and built full account management microfrontend.</li>
                <li>Worked with my second client in 2022 to transition their legacy application to a new React application utilizing federated modules to support multi-team scalability. Integrated SSO authentication and helped build out account management microfrontend. Helped to architect internal design system & component library. Fully built new header, footer, menu, and search components.</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="history-item">
              <h4>Software engineer I to Software engineer II</h4>
              <h5>Wex® - May 2017 to May 2021</h5>
              <ul class="history-details">
                <li>Developed mobile applications using Ionic, Cordova, and Angular. Integrated features like location services and live notifications. Supported with microservices written with Java + Spring.</li>
                <li>Built an ecommerce site using Angular + Material Design. Integrated third & first party APIs using BFF microservice model.</li>
                <li>Helped architect and build a system for incrementally upgrading a legacy application to newer technologies. Integrated new SSO authentication system</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="history-item education">
              <h3>Education</h3>
              <h4>Bachelors of Science in Computer Science</h4>
              <h5>University of Southern Maine - Sept 2013 to May 2017</h5>
              <ul class="history-details">
                <li>Studied lower level engineering, computer mechanics, operating systems, algorithms, and data structures.</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="history-item oss">
              <h3>OSS & side projects</h3>
              <ul class="history-details">
                <li><a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@deepsignal/react">@deepsignal/react</a> is a state management library I built around <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@preact/signals">@preact/signals</a>. If used correctly, it could be the fastest React state management library due to the <a href="https://engineering.deptagency.com/why-i-built-a-new-state-management-library">signal primitive's bypass of the VDOM</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://cakeelizabeth.com/">cakeelizabeth.com</a> is the website for my wife's bakery, written in NextJS</li>
                <li><a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/solid-joystick">solid-joystick</a> is a pluggable joystick component that I built for SolidJS which has has support for multi-touch, mouse-drag, pointer-lock, WASD keys, and physical gamepads</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="about-resume">
          <p>This resume was written entirely in HTML & CSS. See it live at <a href="https://www.standel.io/resume">standel.io/resume</a> or see the source code at <a href="https://www.standel.io/resume-src">standel.io/resume-src</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
<style lang="scss" is:global define:vars={{ check: `url("${Check}")` }}>  
  html, body {
    --primary: #ff00aa;
    --secondary: #0080ff;
    --light: #4d4d4d;
    --lighter: #686868;
    font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: black;
    margin: 0;
    min-height: 100vh;
    width: 100%;

    .container {
      width: 8.5in;
      height: 11in;
      background: white;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .content {
      margin: .5in;
      text-align: justify;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      flex-grow: 1;

      a {
        color: var(--secondary);
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      .intro {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 1em;
        width: 100%;

        h1 > * {
          background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--primary), var(--secondary));
          -webkit-background-clip: text;
          -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        }

        .headshot {
          border: .5em solid var(--primary);
          height: 9em;
          width: 9em;
          border-radius: 5em;
          display: inline-block;

          > img {
            height: 9em;
            width: 9em;
            border-radius: 4.5em;
          }
        }

        .text {
          display: flex;
          flex-direction: column;
          gap: .25rem;
        }

        .name, .title, .about-me {
          margin: 0;
          line-height: 1.15;
        }

        .title {
          color: var(--light);
        }

        .about-me {
          font-size: 9pt;
        }
      }

      .contact {
        padding-top: .5em;
        padding-bottom: .5em;
        padding-left: .5in;
        padding-right: .5in;
        background: azure;
        margin-left: -.5in;
        margin-right: -.5in;
        margin-top: .5em;
        margin-bottom: .5em;
        display: flex;
        ul {
          width: 50%;
          list-style-type: none;
          margin: 0;
          padding: 0;
          li {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 1em;
          }
        }
        p {
          margin: 0;
          line-height: 2.5;
          font-size: 10pt;
        }
        svg {
          height: 25px !important;
          width: 25px !important;
          fill: var(--primary) !important;
        }
      }

      .work-history {
        > ul {
          list-style-type: none;
          margin: 0;
          padding: 0;
        }

        ul.history-details {
          list-style-image: var(--check);

          li::marker {
            font-size: 1.5em;
          }
        }

        h3, h4, h5, p {
          margin: 0;
          line-height: 1.5;
        }
        h4 {
          color: var(--light);
        }
        h5 {
          color: var(--lighter);
        }
        p {
          font-size: 11pt;
        }
        .history-item {
          .history-details {
            font-size: 10pt;
            line-height: 1.25;
            margin-bottom: .5em;
          }
        }
      }

      .about-resume {
        font-size: 8pt;
        display: flex;
        align-items: flex-end;
        justify-content: center;
        text-align: center;
        flex-grow: 1;

        > * {
          max-width: 70%;
        }
        p {
          margin: 0;
          line-height: 1.15;
        }
      }
    }
  }
</style>